DNA cross-linking","Blocks dihydrofolate reductase","Binds to tubulin and prevents microtubule formation","Intercalates with DNA to prevent replication","Inhibits topoisomerase II enzyme"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EVinca alkaloids work by \u003Cstrong\u003Ebinding to tubulin and preventing microtubule formation\u003C/strong\u003E. This disrupts the mitotic spindle assembly, preventing cell division during metaphase. Rapidly-dividing cancer cells   are therefore particularly susceptible to this mechanism of action.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect mechanisms can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECauses DNA cross-linking\u003C/strong\u003E is the mechanism of alkylating agents like cyclophosphamide. These agents form covalent bonds between DNA strands, preventing DNA replication. They are commonly used in lymphomas and solid tumours.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBlocks dihydrofolate reductase\u003C/strong\u003E is the mechanism of methotrexate. It is particularly useful in acute lymphoblastic leukaemia and rheumatoid arthritis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIntercalates with DNA to prevent replication\u003C/strong\u003E describes anthracyclines like doxorubicin. These agents insert between DNA base pairs and are commonly used in breast cancer and lymphomas.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInhibits topoisomerase II enzyme\u003C/strong\u003E refers to drugs like etoposide. By preventing DNA unwinding, these agents block DNA synthesis and are effective in testicular cancer and small cell lung cancer. Anthracyclines also inhibit topoisomerase II.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EExamples of vinca alkaloids include vincristine and vinblastine. Their ability to disrupt microtubule formation makes them particularly useful in treating rapidly proliferating cancers such as leukaemias and lymphomas.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Vinca alkaloids bind to tubulin and prevent microtubule formation, disrupting mitotic spindle assembly.","By preventing cell division, vinca alkaloids are effective against rapidly dividing cancer cells.","Common vinca alkaloids include vincristine and vinblastine."],"references":["Therapeutic Guidelines. Melbourne: Therapeutic Guidelines Limited. Available from: https://www.tg.org.au","Ritter J, Flower RJ (Rod J), Henderson G (Graeme), et al.\u00a0Rang and Dale\u2019s Pharmacology. Tenth edition. Elsevier; 2024.","Australian Medicines Handbook\u00a0(online). Adelaide: Australian Medicines Handbook Pty Ltd. Available from:\u00a0https://amhonline.amh.net.au/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62348"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16786"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62348","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/62348"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-05T14:01:07+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-05T14:01:31+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9477"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76844"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}